Title : Jim Donnelly (politician)
Text : '''James O. Donnelly''' (born 1967) is an American politician and businessperson from [[Presque Isle, Maine]]. Donnelly was elected at age 23 to the [[Maine House of Representatives]] as a [[Maine Republican Party|Republican]]. He served four two-year terms and was unable to seek re-election in 1998 due to the newly initiated term-limits. During his final term in the Legislature, Donnelly was elected Minority Leader of the House of Representatives. At age 30, he was the youngest person to hold such a title in the United States at the time.<ref name="Higgins">{{cite news|url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?nid=2457&dat=19980424&id=AalJAAAAIBAJ&sjid=PQ4NAAAAIBAJ&pg=1391,2628285|title=Term-limited out, Donnelly packs it in|last=Higgins|first=A.J.|date=April 24, 1998|work=[[Bangor Daily News]]|page=A15|accessdate=27 April 2014}}</ref>

In 2002, Donnelly was appointed treasurer of the [[Loring Development Authority]] board of trustees, which oversees the redevelopment of [[Loring Air Force Base]] in [[Limestone, Maine]].<ref name="Brown">{{cite news|url=http://archive.bangordailynews.com/2002/06/18/portland-woman-to-lead-loring-directors/|title=Portland woman to lead Loring directors|last=Brown|first=Wayne|date=June 18, 2002|work=[[Bangor Daily News]]|page=A5|accessdate=27 April 2014}}</ref>

